quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  12,70,"Then, when he had supplied them with their supplies, he placed the drinking-cup in his brother’s saddlebag. Then an announcer called out, “O caravan{1}, most surely you are thieves.”",1:[A metaphor for the people of the caravan.]
  12,71,"They said as they came towards them, “What are you missing?”"
  12,72,"They said, “We are missing the king’s goblet. And whoever comes up with it will have a camel-load, and I{1}guarantee it.”",1:[A grammatical shift from plural to singular.]
  12,73,"They said, “<i>(We swear) </i>by Allah, you<sup>pl </sup>have most surely known that we did not come to spread corruption in the land, and never have we been thieves.”"
  12,74,"They said, “What shall be his repayment, if you<sup>pl </sup>are lying?”"
  12,75,"They said, “The repayment should be that he in whose saddlebag it is found, he himself is the repayment{1}. Thus we repay the unjust ones.”",1:[That he becomes enslaved.]
  12,76,"So he began with their bags before his brother’s bag, then he extracted it from his brother’s bag. Thus We plotted for Joseph; he could not have seized his brother according to the king’s religion{1}unless Allah wills. We elevate by degrees{2}whomever We so will. For above everyone who has knowledge, there is One who is All-Knowing.",1:[The Arabic word used is <i>deen</i> which means ‘a way of life’, ‘religion’ or ‘recompense’.],2:[Qira’at: Nafie’, Ibn Kathir, Abu Amr, Ibn Amer and Abu Ja’far read it as: “We elevate the degrees (ranks) of whomever…” Ya’qub read it as: “He elevates the degrees (ranks) of whomever…”]
  12,77,"They said, “If he steals, well, actually a brother of his has stolen before.” But Joseph kept it secret within himself and did not reveal it to them. He said<i>(to himself) </i>, “You<sup>pl </sup>are in a worse situation, and Allah knows better of what you describe.”"
  12,78,"They said, “O mighty governor, he has a father<i>(who is) </i>a very old man, so take one of us in his place; we see that you are of those who excel in doing good.”"
